  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Disaster Recovery for 11,000 people in Fiji</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">On Friday the 30th of March, the Western Division of Fiji experienced some of the worse flooding in recent history. Today over 11,000 people are living in basic evacuation centres, their homes destroyed by flood waters. Thousands are without electricity and running water. Many people lost their livelihoods and homes in a matter of hours without warning. This projects helps supply immediate basic requirements such as food, clean water and shelter whilst assisting long term recovery efforts.</narrative>
  </description>
